Parliament, Tuesday, 12 June 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services will tomorrow have an engagement with the Public Protector (PP), Adv Busisiwe Mkhwebane, on the Public Protector Rules and Policy on the appointment of a special advisor to the executive authority. Furthermore, the committee will be briefed by Member of Parliament, Mr John Steenhuisen, on the request to expedite procedure to remove the PP from office. Details are as follows: 
	
	Date: Wednesday, 13 June 2018
	Time:  09:30
	Venue: Committee Room M314, Third Floor, Marks Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES, DR MATHOLE MOTSHEKGA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
